history.text: Have you ever seen the movie walle?
I think we are supposed to discuss the movie catch me if you can.
Oh don't think I was told what movie, but sure Ill have to look it up don't think I've seen that one.
It's stars of Leonardo DiCaprio, and Tom Hanks.
ooooo Leonardo... so young then.
Came out in 2002.
Yes, it's based off the true story of Frank Abagnale Junior.

So he uses a fake identity
 to get the information he needs
I'm watching a short plot summary to catch me up on it, looks like a movie I would be interested in watching. Have you seen it?
Yes, he creates many different identities. It also has Christopher Walken in it, I love that guy! He is good in everything he does.
Yes, it is very interesting, and entertaining.
Do you know how long he got away with the fake checks?
It seems like it was like 10 or 15 years.
Carl doesn't seem to like Frank to much, I see he got hired at the same place for check faud.
How funny to be on one side than the other.
Being the bad guy then helping catch them.
Yes, I also just noticed in the cast of that Amy Adams and is in this movie, I had forgotten that.
I don't recognize the name... Let me google what she looks like.
Ah! I know who she is.. red hair.
I like almost everything she's in. You might remember her from enchanted.
YES!
that was my first thought.

Also Jennifer
 garner is in it.
It's pretty interesting how this kid goes from cashing fake checks, to becoming a pilot, and lawyer.
Well it just shows you that if you are determine you can do pretty much anything... at least for awhile. In 2018, I'm not so sure he would have got away with it for so long.
Is this your favorite movie with Leo?
Yes, I think in today's society it would be much harder.
w
My favorite movie with Leo is inception.
What scene do you like most in the movie?
I think the end Oregon Scott, after the Tom Hanks character has search for him so long.

Inception is a good one! Mine would have to be... Django.
.
I like at the very end of this movie they reveal the real frank, and to some details about his life.
I'm watching the part where he pretends to be a FBI agent. He is so smooth with it.
What details?
Like how he's been married for 26 years, had some kids, lives in the Midwest, is still good friends with Carl, and has worked with the FBI to catch a lot of white collar bad guys.
It looks like we're done. It was nice chatting with you about this movie.
